ferok.freeservers.com/head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Who says we can't keep aggro</span><hr size=1> Ive read many threads that say that pallys are mediocre tanks due to their defensive nature, and that they cannot hold aggro in a group situation.  Here is my rebutal.<br>
<br>
Now that I am 40, and I hate hell levels.. and i have this huge urge to go to fear, i decided that i would give the dreadlands a try.  Now i have been a dungeoun fighter my whole career.. from crushbone, to unrest, to mistmoore, to lower guk, to (for just a short time) sol b.  <br>
<br>
So last night im in a group, I am puller, and main tank.  Group consists of the following:<br>
me 40 Palidan<br>
43 Cleric<br>
40ish enchanter (anon)<br>
41 or 42 ranger<br>
42 mage<br>
47 bard<br>
<br>
I was the lowest person in the group.  All of these, with the exception of the mage, are HUGE aggro classes.  I even had the Cleric chain chealing me (fully buffed i was at 1922 hp) for mana efficiency.  <br>
I was able to keep aggro so well, by pulling, attacking, taunting, and attempted disarming, that the chanter and cleric got bored... to the point that they both were nuking and stunning.  <br>
In fact, there were a few times when I had forgotten to turn auto-attack back on when i returned from pulling (this way i dont have to wait for the attack to refresh from a 44 delay), I only noticed it because the drovlarg bastage was occasionally attacking the ranger.<br>
<br>
So if being able to keep a mob off a cleric who is Complete healing, a chanter who was mezzing adds (by the way, only twice did the chanter get aggroed right after mez broke.. both times due to mez breaking naturally), a ranger duel wielding kicking and nuking, a mage nuking, and a bard singing mana song/haste/snare/dot/etc and duel wielding isnt what you call keeping aggro on the tank? Then I wanna see a frickin warrior save the chanters ass with a well placed stun as the mob aggros the chanter whose mez just broke.<br>
<br>
Oh yea.. and the last time i dueled a warrior.. i kicked his arse.<br>
<br>
PALLYS ROCK!<br>
--and for a 3 hour group we had not one death. <p><IMG SRC="http://ferok.freeservers.com/sig.jpg">
